Mauritius’s Domestic Credit Increases 2.1% in April, Central Bank Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-05-31T11:13:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/mauritius-s-domestic-credit-increases-2-1-in-april-central-bank-says.html
Mauritius’s domestic credit, which
includes lending to government, companies and households,
increased 2.1 percent to 307.8 billion rupees in April, the Bank
of Mauritius said.  That compares with a 1 percent decrease in the previous
month, the Port Louis-based central bank said in a statement
published on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
